This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) using neural networks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to control the style of the generated text, which is related to both machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the creation and curation of a large dataset, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
